<Layout::Group {{waypoint "id"}}>

	<Layout::Text text-l text-f>
		<h3><code>meta::id</code></h3>
		<p>The <code>meta::id</code> function extracts and returns the table id from a SurrealDB Record ID.</p>
		<Code @name="docs-surrealql-functions-meta-id.surql" text="API Definition">
			meta::id(record) -> value
		</Code>
		<p>The following example shows this function, and its output, when used in a <Link @link="docs.surrealql.statements.return"><code>RETURN</code></Link> statement:</p>
		<codes vertical>
			<Code @name="docs-surrealql-functions-meta-id-input.surql">
				RETURN meta::id(person:tobie);
			</Code>
			<Code @name="docs-surrealql-functions-meta-id-result.txt">
				"tobie"
			</Code>
		</codes>
	</Layout::Text>

</Layout::Group>

